---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Structured Data and SEO Optimization";
const description = "Implement structured data to improve SEO. Guide to JSON-LD, microdata, and rich snippets for Clodo applications.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <nav class="breadcrumbs">
    <ol>
      <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/">Docs</a></li>
      <li>Structured Data</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Structured Data and SEO</h1>
      <p>Implement structured data to improve search engine visibility and rich snippets.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="content">
    <section>
      <h2>Why Structured Data Matters</h2>
      <p>Structured data helps search engines understand your content better. This leads to:</p>

      <div class="benefits">
        <div class="benefit">
          <strong>Rich Snippets</strong>
          <p>Enhanced search results with ratings, prices, availability</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <strong>Better Rankings</strong>
          <p>Search engines favor content with proper schema markup</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <strong>Knowledge Graph</strong>
          <p>Your content may appear in knowledge panels and carousels</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit">
          <strong>Voice Search</strong>
          <p>Structured data helps voice assistants understand your content</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Schema Vocabulary Types</h2>

      <p>Standard vocabularies for structured data. Common types include:</p>

      <div class="schema-types">
        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>Organization</h3>
          <p>Information about your company or organization</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Company name</li>
            <li>Logo URL</li>
            <li>Website URL</li>
            <li>Contact information</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>Article</h3>
          <p>Blog posts, news articles, and editorial content</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Headline</li>
            <li>Author name</li>
            <li>Date published</li>
            <li>Featured image</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>Product</h3>
          <p>Products for sale with pricing and reviews</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Product name</li>
            <li>Price</li>
            <li>Customer rating</li>
            <li>Stock availability</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>Event</h3>
          <p>Upcoming events with dates and locations</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Event name</li>
            <li>Start date</li>
            <li>Location</li>
            <li>Description</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>LocalBusiness</h3>
          <p>Physical business locations</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Business name</li>
            <li>Street address</li>
            <li>Phone number</li>
            <li>Opening hours</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schema-type">
          <h3>BreadcrumbList</h3>
          <p>Navigation breadcrumbs on pages</p>
          <ul>
            <li>List items</li>
            <li>Position numbers</li>
            <li>Item names</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Implementation Formats</h2>

      <h3>JSON-LD Format</h3>
      <p>JSON-LD is the recommended format for structured data. It is separate from HTML and easy to manage.</p>

      <div class="format-card">
        <strong>Advantages:</strong>
        <ul class="adv-list">
          <li>Separate from HTML markup</li>
          <li>Easy to maintain and update</li>
          <li>Recommended by Google</li>
          <li>Works with JavaScript</li>
          <li>Can be dynamic</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>Microdata Format</h3>
      <p>Microdata integrates directly into your HTML markup using attributes.</p>

      <div class="format-card">
        <strong>Advantages:</strong>
        <ul class="adv-list">
          <li>Integrates with HTML</li>
          <li>Visible structure</li>
          <li>Single source of truth</li>
          <li>Less overhead</li>
          <li>Semantic markup</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>RDFa Format</h3>
      <p>Resource Description Framework in Attributes. Less commonly used but powerful.</p>

      <div class="format-card">
        <strong>Advantages:</strong>
        <ul class="adv-list">
          <li>RDF-based standard</li>
          <li>More flexible</li>
          <li>Linked data support</li>
          <li>Semantic web ready</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Testing and Validation</h2>

      <p>Use these tools to test your structured data implementation:</p>

      <div class="tools">
        <div class="tool">
          <h3>Google Rich Results Test</h3>
          <p>Test how Google renders your page with structured data. Shows errors and warnings.</p>
          <p><strong>URL:</strong> search.google.com/test/rich-results</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool">
          <h3>Schema Validation</h3>
          <p>Validate JSON-LD syntax and schema completeness according to standards.</p>
          <p><strong>URL:</strong> validator.schema.org</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool">
          <h3>Bing Webmaster Tools</h3>
          <p>Test structured data for Bing search results and preview rendering.</p>
          <p><strong>URL:</strong> bing.com/webmaster</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tool">
          <h3>Mobile Friendly Test</h3>
          <p>Test how your structured data appears on mobile devices.</p>
          <p><strong>URL:</strong> search.google.com/test/mobile-friendly</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>SEO Best Practices</h2>

      <div class="practices">
        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Use Accurate Data</h3>
          <p>Structured data should match your visible content. Errors hurt rankings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Keep It Updated</h3>
          <p>Update dates, prices, and availability in real-time. Stale data is worse than no data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Match Your Content</h3>
          <p>Do not add schema for content that is not visible to users. Search engines will penalize this.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Use Correct Types</h3>
          <p>Choose the most specific schema type. Product is more specific than Thing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Include Images</h3>
          <p>Schema types that include images get better rich snippets and CTR improvements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="practice">
          <h3>Validate Regularly</h3>
          <p>Use Google Search Console to monitor structured data errors and issues.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>

      <div class="mistakes">
        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Incorrect Property Names</h3>
          <p>Property names are case-sensitive. Use correct camelCase formatting.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Missing Required Properties</h3>
          <p>Some schema types require specific properties. Check docs for requirements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Wrong Data Types</h3>
          <p>Dates should be ISO 8601 format (2024-01-15), not natural language.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Mixing Formats</h3>
          <p>Use either JSON-LD or Microdata, not both formats on the same page.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Duplicate Schema</h3>
          <p>Do not add the same schema twice. It confuses search engines.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mistake">
          <h3>Hidden Schema</h3>
          <p>Never hide schema in display none or white text. Search engines will penalize this.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Measuring Impact</h2>

      <p>Monitor these metrics to measure schema effectiveness:</p>

      <ul class="metrics-list">
        <li>Click-through rate (CTR) from search results</li>
        <li>Average position in search results</li>
        <li>Rich result appearances</li>
        <li>Knowledge Graph inclusions</li>
        <li>Voice search queries</li>
        <li>Organic traffic growth</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Track these metrics in Google Search Console over time to see improvements.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Learn More</h2>
      <ul class="links">
        <li><a href="https://schema.org/">Schema.org Official Documentation</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/intro-structured-data">Google Structured Data Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/docs/">Clodo Documentation</a></li>
        <li><a href="/examples/">Real-world Examples</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
